    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-09-13T23:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-09-13T23:40:00-05:00" n="222"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d222">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">738.3915/257: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">W. W. Russell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-09-14T00:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 14, 1923—12 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 16—8:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>50. I had long conference yesterday with the President and Minister of Foreign
                    Affairs in regard to the boundary question. The President is taking active steps
                    in the matter and I hope that within a short time something will have been
                    accomplished as to the naming of arbiters to begin negotiations at Port au
                    Prince.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
